isIncorporated

public boolean isIncorporated()
Returns true if and only if this SemanticArgument instance is incorporated by a verb.

Some verbs incorporate information about a particular semantic argument (a semantic argument corresponds to a Frame Element in FrameNet terminology) in their definition: such a semantic argument is called incorporated in FrameNet.
In the case of smile, grimace, frown, pout, and scowl, the affected body part is not separately expressed; it is said to be incorporated. Likewise, in the FrameNet Placing frame, many verbs incorporate the Goal (i.e. the place where the Theme ends up) such as bag.v, bin.v, bottle.v, box.v, cage.v, crate.v, file.v, garage.v.

Returns:
true if this semantic argument is incorporated by a verb, false otherwise
